Describe a program or app on your computer or phone
- When/how you use it
- Where you found it
- And explain how you feel about it

# Youtube
I’d like to talk about an app that I use very often, which is YouTube.

I use this app almost every day, usually in my free time or when I want to relax. For example, I often watch entertainment videos, listen to music, or learn new things through tutorials. Sometimes, I also use it to improve my English by watching videos from native speakers.

I first found YouTube many years ago when I was still a student. At that time, my friends recommended it to me as a great source of both entertainment and learning. Since then, it has become one of the most important apps on my phone.

What I like most about YouTube is the huge variety of content. There are videos about almost everything, from education and technology to travel and daily life. In addition, the app is very easy to use, and it often suggests videos based on my interests, which makes it more enjoyable.

However, one thing I don’t like is that there are quite a lot of advertisements, especially when I use the free version. Sometimes, they can interrupt the videos and be a bit annoying.

Overall, I think YouTube is a very useful and entertaining app, and I can’t really imagine my daily life without it.

# Spotify
I’d like to talk about an app that I use quite regularly, which is Spotify.

I mainly use this app in my free time, especially when I’m relaxing, studying, or commuting. Listening to music helps me focus better and also improves my mood after a long day. Sometimes, I also use it to listen to podcasts when I want to learn something new.

I first found this app a few years ago when one of my friends recommended it to me. At that time, I was looking for a convenient way to listen to music without having to download songs manually. After trying it out, I found it very easy to use, so I decided to keep using it.

What I really like about Spotify is its personalized recommendations. It suggests songs and playlists based on my listening habits, so I often discover new music that matches my taste. In addition, the interface is quite simple and user-friendly, which makes it easy to navigate.

However, one thing I don’t like is that the free version has quite a lot of ads, which can sometimes interrupt the experience. But overall, I still think it’s a very useful and enjoyable app, and I use it almost every day.
